  "prompt": "The current year is 2014. Why is this the 21st century and not the 20th century?",
  "response": "The reason the year 2014 falls in the 21st century rather than the 20th century lies in how centuries are calculated. \n\nCenturies are based on the Gregorian calendar, and a new century begins with a year ending in \"01\". For example, the 20th century began in 1901 and ended in 2000. The 21st century, therefore, began on January 1, 2001, and will end on December 31, 2100.\n\nThe confusion often arises because people sometimes think a new century starts with a year ending in \"00\", but that's not the case. Since 2014 is after 2001, it falls within the 21st century.",
